#include 'template.wml'


<ul class="point">
<li>
QuaD-Pres without WML has three render modes:
</li>
<li>
<b>Server</b> renders the pages for inclusion on a web-server's
static HTML directory.
</li>
<li>
<b>Hard-Disk</b> renders the pages for viewing on a local hard-disk.
</li>
<li>
<b>CGI</b> - it is possible to use a CGI script to dynamically
render the pages.
</li>
<li>
"Server" and "Hard-Disk" modes can be specified in the target types inside
<tt>Render_all_contents.pl</tt>
</li>
</ul>
